text: Caulospongia biflabellata, commonly known as the western staircase sponge, is a species of sea sponge belonging to the family Suberitidae. It is a marine sponge of the temperate waters of Australia (Northwest Cape to Albany, WA).Edgar, Graham J. (2008). Australian Marine Life: The plants and animals of temperate waters (Second ed.).
